intro: Phaeoneuron setosum, commonly known as the hairy phaeoneuron, is a species of flowering plant in the family Apiaceae. It is characterized by its finely hairy stems and leaves, which give it a distinctive appearance. The plant produces small, yellowish-white flowers arranged in umbels, typical of the carrot family. It is native to parts of Europe and Asia and is often found in moist, grassy habitats. Its botanical features make it an interesting subject for ecological and horticultural study.
